==發展==
這部電影由於導演[[羅柏·艾格斯|羅柏·艾格斯]]童年時對[[巫術|巫術]]相當著迷。在不成功的拍攝「太奇怪」、「太模糊」的電影後，艾格斯意識到他必須製作一個更傳統的電影<ref name="Indiewire">{{cite web|last1=Anielski|first1=Ryan|title=How Robert Eggers Combined History and Childhood Horrors in 'The Witch'|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/how-robert-eggers-combined-history-and-childhood-horrors-in-the-witch-20151021|website=Indiewire|accessdate=2016-02-09|archive-date=2016-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160216064532/http://www.indiewire.com/article/how-robert-eggers-combined-history-and-childhood-horrors-in-the-witch-20151021|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他在「問與答」上說「如果我要做一部類型式的電影，它必須是個人式的電影，而且要非常的好<ref name="Indiewire"/>。」製作團隊廣泛於英國與美國博物館，與17世紀農業專家提供諮詢英語合作。<ref>{{cite news|last=Bitel|first=Anton|title=''Voices of the undead: Robert Eggers on The Witch''|url=http://www.bfi.org.uk/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/interviews/robert-eggers-witch|date=2016-03-11|publisher=British Film Institute|accessdate=2016-04-17|archive-date=2016-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160413094331/http://www.bfi.org.uk/news-opinion/sight-sound-magazine/interviews/robert-eggers-witch|dead-url=no}}</ref>

艾格斯想要拍攝新英格蘭的取景照，但是缺乏稅額，他不得不適應加拿大<ref name="Indiewire"/>。事實證明這對艾格斯有一大個問題，因為他找不到該國家的森林環境拍攝<ref name="Indiewire"/>。他不得不離開地圖地標尋找到了一個偏遠極端的地點（位於安大略省的Kiosk）；艾格斯說「最近的小鎮「Hampshire」看起來像大都市。」<ref name="Indiewire"/>

為了給予電影真正的感覺，艾格斯為了拍攝室內的自然光源唯一的燈光只有蠟燭。艾格斯還選擇了「'''VVitch'''」作為電影的標題與海報，他表示，發現這個拼寫出現在一本巫師時代[[詹姆士六世及一世|詹姆士一世時期]]的小說，以及其他期刊。<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bloom|first1=Jessica|title=Designer-Turned-Director Robert Eggers Discusses His Horror Film ‘The Witch’|url=https://www.format.com/magazine/features/design/the-witch-robert-eggers-movie-interview|website=Format Magazine|accessdate=2016-09-26|archive-date=2019-09-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904084011/https://www.format.com/magazine/features/design/the-witch-robert-eggers-movie-interview|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==迴響==
===評價===
《-{zh-tw:女巫;zh-hk:不巫之地;zh-cn:女巫;}-》獲得了正面好評。[[爛番茄|爛番茄]]基於259條評論，持有91%的新鮮度，平均得分為7.8/10<ref>{{Rotten Tomatoes|the_witch_2016}}</ref>。[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]得分高達83<ref name="Meta">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-witch|title=The Witch reviews|website=Metacritic|accessdate=2016-03-09|archive-date=2016-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308074949/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-witch|dead-url=no}}</ref>。據[[CinemaScore|CinemaScore]]調查，觀眾的反應在A+至F間落在「C-」，這與影評人的反應有所落差<ref name="CinemaScore">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/deadpool-risen-the-witch-race-weekend-box-office-1201705730/ |title=‘Deadpool’ Strong With Second Weekend Of $55M; ‘Risen’ Takes $11.8M, ‘Witch’ At $8.7M |work=deadline.com |accessdate=2017-01-07 |archive-date=2018-01-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180103000228/http://deadline.com/2016/02/deadpool-risen-the-witch-race-weekend-box-office-1201705730/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>，相當兩極化。

恐怖作家[[史蒂芬·金|史蒂芬·金]]和{{link-en|布萊恩·凱尼|Brian Keene}}都對這部電影做出了正面的評價，金說「《女巫》嚇死我了。這是一部真正的電影，緊張而發人深省，內心深處。」<ref>{{cite web |author=MrDisgusting |url=http://bloody-disgusting.com/news/3380009/stephen-king/ |title='The Witch' Scared the Hell Out of Stephen King! |website=Bloody Disgusting! |date=2016-02-16 |accessdate=2016-04-26 |archive-date=2016-04-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160421230154/http://bloody-disgusting.com/news/3380009/stephen-king/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> 而凱尼在社交媒體上表示「《女巫》是一部華麗，深思熟慮，可怕的恐怖電影，90％與你們一起在影院的人都太愚蠢無法理解。」<ref>{{cite tweet|user=BrianKeene| author= Keene, Brian| number=701391382275952641 |title=THE VVITCH is a gorgeous, thoughtful, scary horror film that 90% of the people in the theater with you will be too stupid to understand. |date=2016-02-21 |accessdate= 2016-04-26}}</ref> 傑森·科夫曼對那些覺得《女巫》無聊的觀眾表達了沮喪。

===票房===
《女巫》在美國和加拿大的票房總計2510萬美元，其他地區為1530萬美元，全球最終總額為4040萬美元<ref name=BOM />。

在北美，專家預估《女巫》於首週末能從兩千零四十六間戲院中獲得500萬至700萬美元的票房，同週競爭的電影還有《{{le|復活之謎|Risen (2016 film)}}》（預計值為700萬至1200萬美元）與《{{le|奔跑吧，人生|Race (2016 film)}}》（預計值為400萬至700萬美元）<ref name="preview">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/deadpool-race-risen-witch-box-office-preview-1201704419/ |title=‘Deadpool’ Still Cool In Weekend 2 With Superhero Set To Pass $200M – Box Office Preview |work=deadline.com |accessdate=2017-03-02 |archive-date=2017-06-16 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6rGIawA7r?url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/deadpool-race-risen-witch-box-office-preview-1201704419/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《女巫》在上映的當天獲得了330萬美元，首週末總額880萬美元，位居當週票房排名第四<ref name=CinemaScore/>；該週的前三名為《[[惡棍英雄：死侍|惡棍英雄：死侍]]》（5650萬美元）、《[[功夫熊貓3|功夫熊貓3]]》（1250萬美元）和《復活之謎》（1180萬美元）。

===宗教===
《[[Polygon|Polygon]]》的茱莉亞·亞歷山大說「《女巫》中要求人們嘗試與理解在生活中一個虔誠的基督徒生活在孤獨的家庭生活將是什麼樣的感覺，他們違背聖經的話可能會發生可怕的事情。<ref name=Alexander2016>{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2016/2/17/11034540/the-witch-review-a-terrifying-tale-of-depravity|title=The Witch review: A terrifying tale of depravity|last=Alexander|first=Julia|date=2016-02-17|publisher=[[Polygon_(website)|Polygon]]|language=en|accessdate=2016-02-23|archive-date=2016-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160220142159/http://www.polygon.com/2016/2/17/11034540/the-witch-review-a-terrifying-tale-of-depravity|dead-url=no}}</ref>」在《[[大西洋_(雜誌)|大西洋]]》的愛麗莎·威爾金說在[[日舞影展|日舞影展]]中《女巫》與《{{le|耶穌重生路|Last Days in the Desert}}》和《{{le|唐瓦爾迪安|Don Verdean}}》、《{{le|麥可-我的直男前男友|I Am Michael}}》揭示了「宗教複興」，並描述《女巫》：「一個寒冷的日子大約1600年，惡魔拜訪一個虔誠家庭的故事<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2015/03/not-your-typical-god-movie/385315/|title=Can Indie Filmmakers Save Movies About God?|last=Wilkinson|first=Alissa|date=2015-03-18|work=[[The_Atlantic|The Atlantic]]|accessdate=2016-02-23|quote=''[[Last_Days_in_the_Desert|Last Days in the Desert]]'' was the obvious “Bible film” at this year’s Sundance. But the festival’s lineup revealed a resurgence of interest in the religious: In ''[[Don_Verdean|Don Verdean]]'', an affectionately satirical comedy, [[Sam_Rockwell|Sam Rockwell]] stars as a “Biblical archaeologist” who becomes a pawn in a war between two rival local ministers. ''The Witch'', a pristine horror debut from writer/director Robert Eggers, is a chilling circa-1600 story of the devil taking over a devout, Scripture-quoting family. ''[[I_Am_Michael|I Am Michael]]'', executive produced by [[Gus_Van_Sant|Gus Van Sant]], tells the true story of Michael Glatze (played by James Franco), a former gay activist who denounced homosexuality and became a Christian pastor. Other films like ''[[Z_for_Zachariah_(film)|Z for Zachariah]]'' and ''[[Me_and_Earl_and_the_Dying_Girl|Me, Earl, and the Dying Girl]]'' subtly draw on questions and motifs that animate Biblical narratives and questions.|archive-date=2016-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160223013141/http://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2015/03/not-your-typical-god-movie/385315/|dead-url=no}}</ref>」。{{le|Eve Tushnet|Eve Tushnet}}在《{{le|TAC|The American Conservative}}》中的一篇文章中發表了評論，該文章發表在「第一件事」中，描述巫婆對巫術的觀點是「並非修正的主義者」，並進一步指出，這部電影是「被上帝的恐懼瀰漫」。

